      "culture": {
        "title": "Animals in the clan system",
        "body": "Several of the seven Cherokee clans carry animal names — **ᎠᏂᏩᏯ** (Aniwaya, Wolf Clan), the Deer Clan (Anikawi), and the Bird Clan (Anitsisqua). Clan animals are not 'mascots': they reflect traditional responsibilities, such as the Deer Clan's role as fast runners and hunters, and the Bird Clan's role as messengers."
      },
